				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">WARNING!  New mob in FEAR.<a name="21290"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 13 04 2:33 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>http://eqbeastiary.allakhazam.com/search.shtml?id=14217
<br />

<br />
Odds are it is for Berserker epic, but it's killing people off by the dozens.
<br />

<br />
<blockquote><b>Quote:</b><br><span class="quote">
<br />
The Ireblind Imp procs Shocking Aura, which is an unresistable (-1000 resist adjustment) AE mez.  The range on the AE is huge. After mezzing you, the Imp will just wander back to its spot and start regenning like mad. 
<br />

<br />
There are also six mobs named Essence of Rage. These are green at 65, and immune to changes in run speed. They are imps, but not quite as large as the Ireblind Imp. 
<br />

<br />
These new mobs caught us by surprise at the west camp and wiped out three 61+ groups. We were doing a conventional break in to help CR another group that had wiped, and then the Ireblind Imp showed up. Everyone, including pets, was suddenly mezzed. At first, we were all making jokes about it. Then as the mezzes broke, people started getting shadow stepped out of camp by the Imp. Then the Essences of Rage arrived, as did quite a few other roamers. As soon as the mezzes broke, the roamers would all rip into people, but the AE mezz would hit before we could do much of anything. Before long, people started dying. 
<br />

<br />
The Ireblind Imp either spawns at the west camp or corpse camped us. Attempts to kite it out of the camp were unsuccessful, though the Essences of Rage were more than happy to chase people around. This made the CR rather difficult. The range on the AE was so large that it hit me at both the portal and the SW corner. 
<br />

<br />
If we had been ready for the Ireblind Imp, we could have handled it. We had it under 60 percent health even without a strategy. Our problem was that we got caught totally by surprise. 
<br />

<br />
Although the icon for the AE mez is poison, Lucy indicates that the save is against magic.
<br />
</span></blockquote>
<br />
</span></td>
